article.headline: Hawaii takes down UC Riverside 73-52
article.story: HONOLULU -- Isaac Fleming scored 15 points and Stefan Jankovic added 12 to help Hawaii beat UC Riverside 73-52 on Thursday night. The Warriors made 9 of 20 3-pointers compared to 3-of-18 shooting for UC Riverside. The Highlanders were 0 of 9 from distance in the second half. Hawaii (17-9, 5-5 Big West Conference) improved to 9-0 this season following a loss. Roderick Bobbitt had four steals to set Hawaii's single-season record at 85. Jaylen Bland had 13 points for Riverside (11-13, 4-6) and Taylor Johns added 10. Riverside made its first three shots to open an 8-4 lead with 18:13 left, but Steven Thornton's 3-pointer at the 3:23 mark was the Highlanders' next field goal. Hawaii had a 35-20 edge after the 15-minute field-goal drought and led 42-28 at the break. Hawaii led by as many as 24 points.
